<text x="560" y="317" font-family="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" font-size="13" fill="#1e1e1e" text-anchor="end">Response</text>\n  <text x="640" y="547" font-family="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" font-size="13" fill="#1e1e1e">Query</text>\n  <text x="560" y="547" font-family="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" font-size="13" fill="#1e1e1e" text-anchor="end">Result</text>\n</svg>\n```\n\n════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nNow generate the SVG for this diagram description:\n\nIllustrate how the leaf transforms sunlight, water, and carbon dioxide into glucose and oxygen.\nEntities: leaf, water, co2, glucose, oxygen, sun\nNarration: Inside the leaf, a remarkable transformation occurs: it uses the sun’s energy to rearrange water and carbon dioxide molecules into glucose and oxygen. The central leaf is now the site of this invisible factory. Think of this as a recipe: sunlight powers tiny cell machines called chloroplasts, which mix water and carbon dioxide to produce small rings of glucose sugar. Oxygen is created as a convenient byproduct, which the leaf releases into the air. Without sunlight, this conversion grinds to a halt. The key outcome is the plant’s ability to manufacture its own food and provide precious oxygen for other living things.\n\nStyle: stroke="#1e1e1e" on all outlines, fill="#b2f2bb" for key shapes, canvas background always fill="white", font-family="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif".\n\nElement vocabulary:\n  - "sun": type=generic, visual="large filled circle with short radiating lines in all directions representing sunlight", fill=#ffec99, label=\'Sun\'\n  - "leaf": type=generic, visual="rounded-rect with pointed ends and a central curved line to suggest a leaf and vein", fill=#b2f2bb, label=\'Leaf\'\n  - "water": type=generic, visual="group of three overlapping blue teardrop shapes representing water droplets", fill=#a5d8ff, label=\'H₂O\'\n  - "co2": type=generic, visual="three small circles labeled CO₂, arranged in a triangle with faint dashed lines connecting them", fill=#d0bfff, label=\'CO₂\'\n  - "glucose": type=generic, visual="hexagon ring with a thick outline and inner small circles to suggest a sugar molecule", fill=#ffc9c9, label=\'Glucose\'\n  - "oxygen": type=generic, visual="two interlinked small blue circles labeled O₂ to represent an oxygen molecule", fill=#a5d8ff, label=\'O₂\''}], 'model': 'gpt-4.1', 'max_tokens': 8192}}
